  "text": "By abolishing currency and introducing a close substitute on which interest, positive or negative can be paid, the authorities can remove the lower bound on the short nominal interest rate simply by adopting a rule for the nominal interest rate on money like the one given in Eq. (41). Note that if the policy-determined wedge between the two interest rates were zero, ω = 0, Friedman's optimal quantity of money (OQM) rule would be automatically implemented all the time [CITATION_1] .",
